==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precatory
<hw>Prec"a*to*ry</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>precativus</ets>,
<ets>precatorius</ets>, fr. <ets>precari</ets> to pray. See
<er>Precarious</er>.]</ety> <def>Suppliant; beseeching.</def>
<rj><au>Bp. Hopkins.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Precatory words</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>words of
recommendation, request, entreaty, wish, or expectation, employed in
wills, as distinguished from <xex>express directions</xex>; -- in some
cases creating a trust.</cd> <rj><au>Jarman.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precaution</ent>⟦br⟧
